HEPATITIS - MEXICO: (COLIMA) PRISONERS, FATALITIES, REQUEST FOR INFORMATION
***************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 1 Dec 2015
Source: Noticieros TV [machine transl., edited]
http://noticieros.televisa.com/mexico-estados/1512/mueren-5-reos-brote-hepatitis-penal-colima


An outbreak of hepatitis in the Colima Prison Colima kills 5 prisoners who allegedly exchanged syringes injecting heroin. In a statement, the authorities of health and safety in the state reported that there are 20 more who have this same disease. It was reported that the heroin was smuggled into prison by people who hid the drug in parts of the body.

The drug was mixed into the prison with potentially toxic products to dilute it and sell it at a lower price. "They acquire the narcotic inside prices of 5 and 10 pesos, they themselves told me, " said Hermilio Sabino Flores Arias, president of the State Commission Human Rights in Colima.

It is not excluded that the outbreak of hepatitis has also to do with the state and management of food into the prison. "My son showed me some lentils that were in bad condition and he developed severe pain and they thought he was drugged and put in the punishment cell," said the mother of an inmate.

[Byline: Bertha Reynoso]

