[The posting does not state what kind of viral hepatitis is behind the outbreak or indeed whether this is viral hepatitis at all since toxic hepatitis could be at work here. Although more than the 25 cases may have occurred, since cases are often subclinical or at least anicteric (without jaundice) and can be missed but having a case-fatality rate of 20 percent (5 of the 25) would be quite unusual for acute viral hepatitis, for which the fatality rate is generally no more than 1 in 1000. An exception would be if the fatalities were related to superinfection with hepatitis D (delta hepatitis) in individuals who are already carriers of hepatitis B. - Mod.LL

More information on this outbreak would be greatly appreciated. - Mod.MPP

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3842838,4419.]
